  "texts": [
    "We defined the most important time windows separately for the target classes (Fig. 5).",
    "While the pattern looked similar for scrambled and blurred stimuli with a peak roughly around 150 ms (156.25 and 148.44 ms, respectively) and a summed SHAP value of roughly 0.056 (0.0566 and 0.0555, respectively), the pattern for face stimuli differed considerably.",
    "It shows two pronounced peaks at 162.11 and 292.97 ms, both reaching a summed SHAP value of nearly 0.04 with the later peak being a little higher (0.0388) than the former (0.0381).",
    "At the later peak as defined by the face condition, blurred and scrambled faces did not exhibit a local maximum (both 0.0313).",
    "For each of the four mentioned peaks (two for faces, and one each for blurred and scrambled stimuli), we created a time window and analyzed which electrodes contributed most to the classification."
